																		Finding the Scarlet King&#039;s children.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drblackbox" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2785951); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2785951&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610246440" alt="Drblackbox" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2785951)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drblackbox" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2785951); return false;" >Drblackbox</a></span> <span class="odate time_1543169901 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">25 Nov 2018 18:18</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4067641">
									

<p>According to <a href="/scp-231">SCP-231</a> each of the children are intended to give birth to somepart of a deity, with the seeming intent to undo Jesus Christ's teachings as a sort of &quot;anti-Christ&quot;. Interestingly all of these children were designated with a 2-intiger SCP number, which doesn't exist. But maybe it <em>did</em> exist.</p>
<p>We know from <a href="/scp-233">SCP-233</a> (which not only effects pregnant humans but is also part of Clef's research) that the 3/4-digit system isn't how the foundation had always operated and from the twistedgears/kaktus proposal that the Foundation used to classify &quot;separate&quot; objects in different slots. So in theory SCP-048 could have been shortened to SCP-48.</p>
<p>Basically I'm suggesting each of the products of SCP-231 are in some way the &quot;7 deadly sins&quot; with the intended purpose of causing an the third worst K-class Scenario (XK, total failure of human morality).</p>
<ul>
<li>The Light Bringer aka Lucifer the Fallen Angel: <a href="/scp-2030">SCP-2030</a>, It's a rather unorthodox take but still holds the same core concepts.</li>
<li>SCP-231-1 (Lust): The most simplistic and ultimately least dangerous child, <a href="/scp-106">SCP-106</a> or as it was called SCP-16 is a powerful reality warping entity that only uses it's powers for weird semi-sexual desires with no regard for who or what is destroyed in the process.</li>
<li>SCP-231-2 (Wrath): <a href="/scp-682">SCP-682</a> another reality-warping entity able to change it's own structure to adapt to nearly anything it wants has seemingly lost all drive beyond &quot;getting back&quot; at humanity, possibly for Procedure 110-Montauk.</li>
<li>SCP-231-3 (Greed): <a href="/scp-035">SCP-035</a> is capable of giving those who wear it untold power and knowledge, but consumes their minds until they are nothing more than a flailing piece of meat for SCP-035 to use.</li>
<li>SCP-231-4 (Envy): Due to it's exposure to SCP-500 <a href="/scp-447">SCP-447</a> is effectively dead and a substance rather than a lifeform. However consider the term *green with envy*.</li>
<li>SCP-231-5 (Sloth): <a href="/scp-2774">SCP-2774</a> is again an entity that consumes the mind, ultimately capable of wining when the infect give into the urge to give up and rest.</li>
<li>SCP-231-6 (Pride): <a href="/scp-4666">SCP-4666</a> or as it's more commonly known as &quot;Santa Claus&quot; isn't an actual physical being as much as an idea. All the traditions and &quot;themes&quot; related to Christmas are in some way a projection of it with the exception of the color green. In 1971 the Foundation used advanced computer-science to create a counter-meme that goes along with SCP-4666's red. In the end it's the idea that humans can create a &quot;better&quot; Christmas around gifts and happiness rather than the celebration of the ideal human's birth.</li>
<li>SCP-231-7 (Gluttony): The entity is yet to be born but it can be assumed that along with it's 7 brothers it will bring the end of human morality and sapient thought.</li>
</ul>

