														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4068552">
									

<p>To make things even more convoluted, because that's what we're here for, let's consider that SCP-231 was an experiment by Children of the Scarlet King to <em>imitate</em> the Seven Brides&#8212;presumably A'tivik through A'habbat you've mentioned. It's possible 231 was actually wed by Scarlet King, but it's also entirely possible they're just infused with the King's essence, mutating the child they already have prior of the experiment.</p>
<p>There's also the fact that there's no rule mentioning that there are only seven beings that will ever be the Seven Bride: there's the possibility that unlike the King, the Brides are not immortal, and throughout his existence the King had sired many more children with many sets of Seven Brides.</p>

							</div>

								
					
