			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4853731">
									

<p>In the Serpent's Hand Hub, SCP-017 is called the Second Child which I assume is the second child of the Scarlet King. Also Summer's Exile which is about SCP-682 mentions the Fifth Child which suggests SCP-053, and my theory is the reason that those two get along is because they are siblings, or at least half-siblings, with SCP-682 being first generation and SCP-053 being second generation from the same father, the Scarlet King.</p>
<p>And then of course, there's the story about SCP-999 being the seventh child, which now accounts for three of the six surviving children, assuming the fourth is still dead. My guess is SCP-239 and SCP-040 are two others, and while I doubt it could work by context, I think it would be intesting to reveal SCP-105 is actually the first child of the Scarlet King and that Team Iris of Alpha-9 is critical in defeating him the next time he breaks free.</p>

							</div>

								
					
